{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"53c5ea51-6392-465e-a7d1-f845b79665d0","content":"Let me also check if there's a packaging project (`.csproj` or `.nuspec`) for creating the NuGet package.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_9mc7q0TrlgBnH2Mx8DK3ad","name":"glob","arguments":{"pattern":"**/*.{csproj,nuspec,nupkg}"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"**/*.{csproj,nuspec,nupkg}"}],"interactionId":"b412d547-c352-4597-91b0-7238d9232ce5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nKey things to check:\n1. `$schema` - Missing. It's recommended to include the schema URL.\n2. `identity` - Present ✓\n3. `name` - Present ✓\n4. `shortName` - Present ✓\n5. `sourceName` - Present ✓\n6. `author` - Present ✓\n7. `classifications` - Present ✓\n8. `tags` - Present with language and type ✓\n9. `symbols` - Present ✓\n\n\n10. `preferNameDirectory` - Not present (optional)\n11. `groupIdentity` - Missing. This is important for NuGet publishing to group related templates.\n12. `precedence` - Not present (optional but useful with groupIdentity)\n\nI'm also noticing that `description` is missing, which isn't strictly required by the engine but matters significantly for discoverability on NuGet. I should check whether there's a .nupkg or .csproj file handling the template packaging.","outputTokens":398,"requestId":"93C4:3F23E5:E300122:F92F490:69F2A94F"},"id":"9ae1c1e9-a8d2-45b3-a3ba-253082d786ee","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:59:04.668Z","parentId":"a1cc018b-cdb3-4b36-91cf-8a7b9700217f"}
